To resolve the error message "Property 'file' does not exist on type 'Request<ParamsDictionary, any, any, ParsedQs, Record<string, any>>'", you can do the following:

1. Import the necessary packages:
```typescript
import { Request, Response } from 'express';
import multer from 'multer';
```

2. Create a storage configuration for multer:
```typescript
const storage = multer.diskStorage({
  destination: (req, file, cb) => {
    // Define the destination folder where the uploaded files will be stored
    cb(null, 'uploads/');
  },
  filename: (req, file, cb) => {
    // Define the file name for the uploaded file
    cb(null, file.originalname);
  }
});

const upload = multer({ storage: storage });
```

3. Define your API route with file upload functionality:
```typescript
app.post('/upload', upload.single('file'), (req: Request, res: Response) => {
  // Access the uploaded file using req.file
  if (!req.file) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'No file uploaded' });
  }

  // Process the uploaded file
  // ...

  return res.status(200).json({ message: 'File uploaded successfully' });
});
```
In this example, we are using a single file upload field named 'file' in the HTML form. Adjust the field name as per your form configuration.

Make sure you have created an "uploads" folder in your project root directory where the uploaded files will be stored.

Note: This solution assumes you are using TypeScript and Express.js for your API.

